<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1901,2001]" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1938,1964]" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other members of the genus by male genitalia characters. It is possible that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[299,397,1975,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Grammacephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugio">
<emphasis box="[299,397,1975,2001]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">G. pugio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[589,804,1975,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Grammacephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveimarginatus">
<emphasis box="[589,804,1975,2001]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">G. niveimarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the male of the latter species is unknown so far.
</paragraph>
